.TH "TRANSITIONEVENT.PSEUDOELEMENT" "3JS" "November 7, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TransitionEvent.pseudoElement \- TransitionEvent: pseudoElement property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]TransitionEvent.pseudoElement\f[B]\f[R] read\-only
property is a string, starting with \f[CR]\(aq::\(aq\f[R], containing
the name of the pseudo\-element the animation runs on.
If the transition doesn\(cqt run on a pseudo\-element but on the
element, an empty string: \f[CR]\(dq\(dq\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A string.
